<div class="lesson-content">

	<CustomSection title={"Consume This! Collaborative Slam Poetry for a Sustainable Future"} content={"<strong>(30-60 MINUTES)</strong>"} {sdgColor} />

	<CustomSection title={"Materials:"} content={"<p>Audio<br>Whiteboard or large chart paper<br>Markers<br>Notebooks or paper<br>Pens/Pencils</p>"} {sdgColor} />

	<Introduction content={"<p>Begin with an introduction to slam poetry. Explain that it’s a dynamic form of performance poetry that combines elements of spoken word, theater, and audience interaction.<br>Highlight its characteristics:\n<ul>\n<li>Emphasis on personal expression and social commentary.</li>\n<li>Use of rhythm, rhyme, repetition, and wordplay.</li>\n<li>Energetic delivery and emotional intensity.</li>\n<li>Focus on connecting with the audience.</li>\n</ul><br>Show short exerpts from diverse slam poetry performances, focusing on\n<ul>\n<li>Different styles and themes.</li>\n<li>The power of spoken word to evoke emotions and inspire action.</li>\n</ul><br><em>Examples:</em>\n<ul>\n<li>Sarah Kay, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mlter5esJ88\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“Forest Fires”</a></li>\n<li>Rudy Francisco, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GOjHUC0Udo4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“My Honest Poem”</a></li>\n<li>Sunni Patterson, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jcuRce32qsM\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“We Know This Place”</a></li>\n<li>Aranya Johar ft Samuel, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6RkIZ0P3U8E\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“Buy Now or Panic Later”</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4DpE2zbH_Iw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“Evolution”</a>, Solli Raphael</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fLTG6GGEk1g\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">“Beauty Queen”</a>, Rich Story</li>\n</ul><br>Facilitate a brief discussion.\n<ul>\n<li>What are your initial impressions of slam poetry?</li>\n<li>How does it differ from traditional poetry?</li>\n<li>What makes slam poetry so engaging and impactful?</li>\n</ul><br>Introduce or reintroduce Global Goal 12: Responsible Consumption and Production, and emphasize its importance in achieving a sustainable future.<br>Explain that all groups will be working together to explore Global Goal 12 as a whole.<br>Facilitate a discussion about the interconnectedness of the targets within Global Goal 12:\n<ul>\n<li>How do issues like food waste, resource depletion, and corporate responsibility relate to each other?</li>\n<li>How does our individual consumption impact global production patterns?</li>\n<li>What are the systemic changes needed to achieve sustainable consumption and production?</li>\n</ul><br>Provide a brief overview of key themes and concerns addressed by Global Goal 12:\n<ul>\n<li>Waste reduction and recycling.</li>\n<li>Efficient use of natural resources.</li>\n<li>Sustainable business practices.</li>\n<li>Consumer awareness and education.</li>\n<li>Policy and government action.</li>\n</ul><br>Connect slam poetry and Global Goal 12 by engaging students in a thought-provoking discussion about how slam poetry can be used to explore themes of consumption and production. Ask questions like\n<ul>\n<li>How can the raw emotion and energy of slam poetry capture the urgency of the environmental crisis?</li>\n<li>Can slam poetry challenge listeners to rethink their relationship with material goods and the systems of production that create them?</li>\n<li>How can spoken word be a powerful tool for raising awareness and inspiring action for sustainable change?</li>\n<li>How can we use slam poetry to give voice to the planet, to marginalized communities, or to future generations?</li>\n</ul></p>"} />

	<CustomSection title={"Exploring Slam Poetry Techniques and Collaborative Brainstorming"} content={"<p>Demonstrate and discuss key slam poetry techniques that students can incorporate into their writing:\n<ul>\n<li><em>Personal Narrative:</em> Sharing personal experiences related to consumption, waste, or sustainability.</li>\n<li><em>Social Commentary:</em> Critiquing unsustainable practices, corporate greed, or government inaction.</li>\n<li><em>Imagery and Metaphor:</em> Using vivid language and figurative language to create powerful visuals and evoke emotions.</li>\n<li><em>Rhythm and Rhyme:</em> Employing rhythm, rhyme, repetition, and alliteration to create a musical flow and emphasize key points.</li>\n<li><em>Call and Response:</em> Engaging the audience with questions or refrains.</li>\n<li><em>Performance Elements:</em> Using voice modulation, body language, and stage presence to enhance the impact of the poem.</li>\n</ul><br>Groups brainstorm together to develop a single slam poem that addresses Global Goal 12. Encourage students to:\n<ul>\n<li>Identify key themes and messages related to responsible consumption and production.</li>\n<li>Brainstorm different perspectives and voices to include in the poem (e.g., a consumer, a worker, a scientist, the planet).</li>\n<li>Explore different ways to structure the poem (e.g., a narrative, an argument, a call to action).</li>\n<li>Divide the poem into sections or stanzas that can be performed by different group members.</li>\n<li>Explore different ways to incorporate each group member’s voice and style.</li>\n</ul><br>Examples of thematic approaches:\n<ul>\n<li>A poem that traces the lifecycle of a product, from resource extraction to disposal, with different group members voicing different stages.</li>\n<li>A poem that contrasts unsustainable and sustainable lifestyles, with different members embodying each approach.</li>\n<li>A poem taht critiques the influence of advertising on consumer behavior, with different members taking on the roles of advertising and consumers.</li>\n<li>A poem that calls for systemic change in production and consumption patterns, with different members highlighting specific solutions (e.g., circular economy, renewable energy, policy reform).</li>\n<li>A poem that explores the personal and emotional impact of the climate crisis, connecting individual actions to global consequences.</li>\n</ul><br>Groups create a basic outline or structure for their collaborative slam poem, assigning sections or roles to different members.</p>"} {sdgColor} />

	<CustomSection title={"Collaborative Poem Writing and Rehearsal"} content={"<p>Groups work together to write their slam poem, with each member contributing. Emphasize:\n<ul>\n<li>Clear communication and active listening within the group.</li>\n<li>Respectful sharing of ideas and constructive feedback.</li>\n<li>Building upon each other’s language, imagery, and rhythm.</li>\n<li>Creating a cohesive flow and tone throughout the poem.</li>\n<li>Ensuring each group member has a meaningful and impactful part to perform that they are comfortable with.</li>\n<li>The importance of creating a shared vision and working towards a common goal.</li>\n</ul><br>Circulate to provide guidance, facilitate collaboration, and help resolve any issues when needed.<br>Groups rehearse their poems collaboratively, focusing on:\n<ul>\n<li>Smooth transitions between different sections and performers.</li>\n<li>Coordinated vocal delivery, rhythm, and pacing.</li>\n<li>Effective use of group dynamics.</li>\n<li>Ensuring each member feels confident, prepared, and supported by their group.</li>\n<li>Practicing eye contact, gestures, and other performance elements to connect with the audience.</li>\n</ul><br>Provide constructive feedback on both the writing and the performance as a group, offering specific suggestions for improvement.</p>"} {sdgColor} />

	<CustomSection title={"Collaborative Poem Performances"} content={"<p>Groups perform their collaborative slam poems for the class. Encourage:\n<ul>\n<li>A sense of collective energy, shared purpose, and mutual support.</li>\n<li>Clear, engaging, and powerful delivery from each performer.</li>\n<li>Effective use of group dynamics and staging to create a visually and emotionally compelling performance.</li>\n</ul><br>Facilitate a supportive and encouraging environment, celebrating the groups’ efforts and achievements.<br>After each performance, the class offers positive feedback and constructive criticism, focusing on:\n<ul>\n<li>The effectiveness of the poem as a whole, including its message, structure, and impact.</li>\n<li>The collaboration, coordination, and energy of the performers as a group.</li>\n<li>The use of slam poetry techniques and performance elements.</li>\n</ul></p>"} {sdgColor} />

	<CustomSection title={"Reflection and Summary"} content={"<p>Have students reflect on their learning experience through discussion or writing.<br>Ask guiding questions like:\n<ul>\n<li>How did the collaborative process of writing and performing a slam poem help you explore the complexities of responsible consumption and production?</li>\n<li>What did you learn about the power of rhythm, rhyme, and performance in slam poetry to communicate urgent messages about sustainability?</li>\n<li>Did the act of giving voice to different perspectives (e.g., consumer, worker, planet) within the poem deepen your understanding of the issues?</li>\n<li>How did creating a slam poem as a group differ from individual creative writing, and what were the benefits or challenges of that collaboration?</li>\n<li>What did you discover about your own ability to express complex ideas and emotions through spoken word and body language?</li>\n<li>What new insights did you gain about Global Goal 12 and the importance of sustainable consumption and production patterns through this poetic exploration?</li>\n<li>How did the themes and messages that emerged from your poem, and those of other groups, highlight the interconnectedness of issues like waste, resource use, and corporate responsibility?</li>\n<li>Did the activity make you think differently about your own role in consumption and its impact on the planet?</li>\n<li>How can giving voice to environmental issues through art contribute to broader social change?</li>\n<li>What specific challenges or solutions related to Global Goal 12 do you feel were most effectively conveyed through the slam poetry format?</li>\n<li>Did participating in this slam poetry experience make you feel more empowered to advocate for sustainable practices? Why or why not?</li>\n<li>What is one key takeaway about responsible consumption and the power of creative expression that you will remember from this lesson?</li>\n<li>How has this lesson influenced your thinking about your own consumer choices and their broader impact?</li>\n</ul></p>"} {sdgColor} />

	<CustomSection title={"Assessment"} content={"<ul>\n<li>Consistent and enthusiastic involvement in all phases of the lesson, including initial brainstorming, understanding slam poetry techniques, collaborative writing, rehearsal, and class discussions.</li>\n<li>Comprehension of Global Goal 12 themes (e.g., waste reduction, sustainable production, consumer awareness) as demonstrated through the thematic content and symbolism within the collective slam poem(s) and the verbal explanations.</li>\n<li>Originality and effectiveness in crafting collaborative slam poetry, including use of rhythm, rhyme, imagery, metaphor, and voice modulation to convey the message about responsible consumption.</li>\n<li>How clearly and powerfully the finished slam poem communicates its intended message about Global Goal 12. Did the collective performance successfully evoke thought or emotion in the audience?</li>\n<li>Ability to work effectively within groups, demonstrating active listening, respectful sharing of ideas, and cohesive collaboration during the writing and rehearsal process.</li>\n<li>Energy, clarity, and coordination of the group’s performance, including vocal delivery, body language, and the smooth transitions between individual sections, to enhance the poem’s impact.</li>\n<li>Nuance and insight demonstrated in reflections, particularly concerning the role of performance poetry in advocating for sustainable development and the complexities of consumption patterns.</li>\n</ul>"} {sdgColor} />

</div>
